1. Svi *očekuju* da će se danas vreme popraviti. (Everyone expects that the weather will improve today.)
2. Naši klijenti *očekuju* kvalitetnu uslugu i podršku. (Our clients expect quality service and support.)
3. Kada se vratim kući, moji roditelji *očekuju* da im pripremim večeru. (When I come back home, my parents expect me to prepare dinner for them.)
4. Nismo *očekivali* da će cena biti tako visoka. (We didn't expect the price to be so high.)
5. *Očekujem* tvoj odgovor na moj mejl. (I'm expecting your reply to my email.)
6. Ako želiš da dobiješ dobru ocenu, moraš *očekivati* da ćeš morati mnogo da učiš. (If you want to get a good grade, you have to expect that you'll have to study a lot.)
7. Ona je *očekivala* da će dobiti unapređenje, ali nije uspela. (She expected to get promoted, but she didn't succeed.)
8. *Očekivanja* su mu bila prevelika, pa je bio razočaran kada nije ostvario svoj cilj. (His expectations were too high, so he was disappointed when he didn't achieve his goal.)
9. Nema smisla *očekivati* da će se sve promeniti preko noći. (There's no point in expecting everything to change overnight.)
10. Da bi se izbegli nesporazumi, važno je jasno *očekivati* od drugih šta se od njih očekuje. (To avoid misunderstandings, it's important to clearly expect from others what is expected of them.)